	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=82561><span id= >tzsjynx</span></a><br><span id=notbold>274 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.03]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A good paladin (by good I mean a lot of AAs =P) will NEVER be able to do more damage using a one handed weapon over a two-handed weapon unless the two are EXTREMELY mismatched.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its a plain and simple fact... Paladins get Innate Bonuses to 2hs and 2hp weapons, they then proceed to get AAs that allow them to Strike 2 extra times, Bash, Tripple Reposte, and Increase Double Attack numbers while weilding a two-hander via AA.<br><br>The reason high end Paladins use one-handers is never for damage, but for defensive capabilities.  The best two-handers in the game have what... 225 HP 50 AC... and those are DEFENSIVE two-handers.  With a Sword and Shield a Time-Geared Paladin can reach ends of 400 HP 100 AC and usually doubled attributes and resists.  The fact that this is a defensive weapon is only amplified by the fact that it Procs a 150 point Group heal.<br><br>Find a Paladin that claims they can pull off more damage with this and a shield and you just found yourself a Paladin that thinks he's good but isn't =).  But Hell I'd use this and a shield over a two-hander any day of the week if I found myself having trouble tanking.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Warning - Attempting to patch together any coherent message from my posts may result in chronic headaches and/or intense vomitting.</td></tr>
